<section class="sample-entries" id="sample-entries">
  <h2 class="section-title">See What SATrack Generates</h2>
  <p class="seciton-sub">Every word gets a mnemoinic, a picture story, and an example sentence, all AI-generated with retrival-augmented generation for quality.</p>

  <div class="sample-entries-grid">
    <a href="/vocab/ACCOLADE" class="sample-entry">
      <div class="entry-word">ACCOLADE</div>
      <div class="entry-pos">Noun</div>
      <div class="entry-def">an award, or praise</div>
      <div class="entry-mnemonic">(AKK-oh-lade) Sounds like: echo lad</div>
      <div class="entry-pic">A young boy is standing on the edge of a cliff, facing a vertical wall of rock. He yells wonderful things about himself so that his voice echoes off the wall and comes back to him.</div>
      <div class="entry-example">The film received accolades from both the critics and the general public.</div>
      <span class="entry-link"> See Full Entry</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/vocab/AFFIRMATION" class="sample-entry">
      <div class="entry-word">AFFIRMATION</div>
      <div class="entry-pos">Noun</div>
      <div class="entry-def">positive statement; assertion; agreement</div>
      <div class="entry-mnemonic">(aff-er-MAY-shun) Sounds like: a firm Asian</div>
      <div class="entry-pic">A muscular man from the Orient being interviewed by a TV news reporter. “We’ve heard,” says the reporter, “that you plan to break the world weightlifting record by lifting a Toyota filled with Sumo wrestlers. Is this true?” “Yes,” replies the Asian man. “And that includes a full tank of gas and maps in the glove compartment.” Looking into the TV camera, the reporter says, “Up until now it had been just another unfounded rumor. But now we’ve received affirmation.”</div>
      <div class="entry-other-forms">Affirm (verb); affirmative (adj); affirmatively (adv)</div>
      <div class="entry-example">The prime minister saw her re-election as an affirmation of her policies.</div>
      <span class="entry-link"> See Full Entry</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/vocab/RECAPITULATE" class="sample-entry">
      <div class="entry-word">RECAPITULATE</div>
      <div class="entry-pos">Verb</div>
      <div class="entry-def">to summarize or repeat the main points of something</div>
      <div class="entry-mnemonic">(ree-kuh-PICH-uh-late) Sounds like: re-CAPE-it-u-late</div>
      <div class="entry-pic">A superhero is giving a press conference. After explaining his plan to save the city from a giant lizard, a reporter says, “Could you say that again more simply?” The hero sighs, pulls his CAPE up tight (re-CAPE), and repeats his main points in order for the journalists to understand. He is summarizing (recapitulating) his argument.</div>
      <div class="entry-other-forms">Recapitulation (noun), Recapitulative (adjective)</div>
      <div class="entry-example">The lawyer recapitulated the key evidence for the jury before resting her case.</div>
      <span class="entry-link"> See Full Entry</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/vocab/SAGACIOUS" class="sample-entry">
      <div class="entry-word">SAGACIOUS</div>
      <div class="entry-pos">Adjective</div>
      <div class="entry-def">having sharp judgment and wisdom; shrewd</div>
      <div class="entry-mnemonic">(sag-AY-shus) Sounds like: sage with a spacious mind</div>
      <div class="entry-pic">A wise old sage, wearing a pointy wizard hat, sits in a vast, spacious library filled from floor to ceiling with books. He closes one eye and points a knowing finger, having just solved a complex riddle with ease.</div>
      <div class="entry-other-forms">Sagacity (noun), Sagaciously (adverb)</div>
      <div class="entry-example">Her sagacious investment advice saved the company from a disastrous market crash.</div>
      <span class="entry-link"> See Full Entry</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/vocab/PERNICIOUS">
      <div class="entry-word"> PERNICIOUS </div>
      <div class="entry-pos"> Adjective </div>
      <div class="entry-def"> having a harmful effect, especially in a gradual or subtle way </div>
      <div class="entry-mnemonic"> (per-NISH-us) Sounds like: a poisonous fish named Percy</div>
