<section class="story-section" id="story">
  <div class="story-content">
    <h2 class="section-title">Why I Built This?</h2>
    <p class="story-lead">
      I was studying for the SAT, frustrated. Every vocabulary app felt like flashcards with extra steps, every practice tool either had stale questions or wanted $5000/month. None of them <em>adapted</em> to what I actually didn't know.
    </p>
    <p>
      So I built SATrack: a tool that uses retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) to create vocabulary entries that actually stick. When you look up a word, the system searches its database for the most relevant existing entries, feeds them to an AI as context, and generates a mnemonic, picture, story and example scentence that are grounded in real quality examples.
    </p>
    <p>This isn't a company. It's a student project built with Supabase, OpenAI-compitable APIs, and a lot of late nights. Every feature exists because I needed it myself. If it helps you too, that's enough for me.</p>
    <!-- Will edit this section, I want the story to be like why I built it and what was the motive, what was te thought process and how it helps -->
  </div>
</section>